come the region’s major power, including a decades-long war against the Mohegans led by Uncas, Ninigret’s archrival. To offset growing English power, Ninigret formed long-distance alliances with the powerful Mohawks of the Iroquois League and the Pocumtucks of the Connecticut River Valley. Over the course of Ninigret’s life, English officials repeatedly charged him with plotting to organize a coalition of tribes and even the Dutch to roll back English settlement. Ironically, though, Ninigret refused to take up arms against the English in King Philip’s War. Ninigret died at the end of the war, having guided his people through one of the most tumultuous chapters of the colonial era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aNarragansett IndiansxPolitics and governmenty17th century. 0aNiantic IndiansxKings and rulersvBiography. 4aEarly American & Colonial History. 4aNative American Studies. 4aU.S. History.  a17th century New England.  aAnthropology.  aColonialism.  aDecolonization.  aIndigenous.  aNative American geopolitical landscape.  aNative Americans.  aUnited Colonies of New England.  abiographies of important native americans.  abiographies of native americans.  acolonial histories.  acolonial history.  acolonial new englanders.  aearly american history.  aearly american settler history.  aenemies of the pe".  afighting the pe" indians.  ahelp from the native americans.  ahistories of indigenous people.  ahistory of colonial americans with indians.  ahistory of naragansett.  ahistory of new england indians.  ahistory of the new england colonies.  aindians of narragansett.  ajuanemo.  alife of ninigret.  anative american demographic studies.  anative american history.  anative american studies.  anative politics.  anew england indians.  aniantic indian